[30;1m823 | [0m[35m* Support for out of tree can interfaces with pluggy.[0m
[30;1m824 | [0m[35m* Initial support for CAN-FD for socketcan_native and kvaser interfaces.[0m

[30;1m5 | [0m[35mabstractions to different hardware devices, and a basic suite of utilities for sending and[0m
[30;1m6 | [0m[35mreceiving messages on a CAN bus. Other tools are available that either extend the functionality[0m

[30;1m245 | [0m[35mThe ``socketcan`` interface implements thin wrappers to the linux `broadcast manager`[0m
[30;1m246 | [0m[35msocket api. This allows the cyclic transmission of CAN messages at given intervals.[0m
[30;1m247 | [0m[35mThe overhead for periodic message sending is extremely low as all the heavy lifting occurs[0m
[30;1m248 | [0m[35mwithin the linux kernel.[0m
